body_content.explanation: arranged to happen, be done, or be used at a particular time in the future:
examples: The restaurant opens four times a week for pre-booked dinners only.
Our prebooked taxi arrived at 6.30 in the morning.
Their clubhouse was prebooked for a wedding reception.

body_content.explanation: A pre-booked person or group has arranged to have or do something at a particular time in the future:
examples: Pre-booked groups can visit the museum at discount prices.
40,000 people were prebooked for the vaccine.
